 Current guidelines for the prevention of cardiovascular disease recognize the major interest of an optimal control of all cardiovascular risk factors.

 It includes high blood pressure reduction, dietetic measures (weight loss - control of dyslipidemia and diabetes - regular physical activity), smoking cessation, stress management, .

