 The aim of this randomized controlled trial is to evaluate the efficacy of a dedicated therapeutic education program to control blood pressure and other cardiovascular risk factors in general practice patients at high cardiovascular risk.

 250 patients are being enrolled.

 All patients will receive standard care but only 125 patients (randomized 1 to 1) will receive a structured therapeutic education program.

